And finally, I have block 2.

00:05:47.180 --> 00:05:50.850
So I'll draw that over here.

00:05:50.850 --> 00:05:53.230
I'll write block 2.

00:05:53.230 --> 00:05:57.170
In fact, let's say
a little space here.

00:05:57.170 --> 00:05:59.750
We'll have j hat B downwards.

00:05:59.750 --> 00:06:02.430
Now block 2, what
do we have there?

00:06:02.430 --> 00:06:04.770
We have the string
pulling up block 2,

00:06:04.770 --> 00:06:08.760
which we've identified as T3.

00:06:08.760 --> 00:06:11.670
And we have the gravitational
force on block 2

00:06:11.670 --> 00:06:14.450
downward, M2 g.

00:06:14.450 --> 00:06:17.220
And there we have j had 2.

00:06:17.220 --> 00:06:21.400
So I've now drawn the free body
diagram of the various objects.

00:06:21.400 --> 00:06:24.460
And that enables me to
apply Newton's second law

00:06:24.460 --> 00:06:26.410
for each of these objects.

00:06:26.410 --> 00:06:27.520
So let's begin.

00:06:27.520 --> 00:06:29.720
We'll start with object 1.

00:06:29.720 --> 00:06:33.920
We have-- remember in all
cases, we're going to apply F

00:06:33.920 --> 00:06:35.880
equals m a.

00:06:35.880 --> 00:06:41.860
So for object 1, we have
