00:07:25.350 --> 00:07:29.670
this is zero even
though pulley A may

00:07:29.670 --> 00:07:32.880
be-- it's actually fixed too.

00:07:32.880 --> 00:07:34.310
So it's not even accelerating.

00:07:34.310 --> 00:07:36.930
And what we see here
is this equation--

00:07:36.930 --> 00:07:39.510
I'm going to quickly
note that it tells us

00:07:39.510 --> 00:07:47.270
that the string holding pulley
2 up, T2, is equal to 2T.

00:07:47.270 --> 00:07:49.890
So we can think of if,
we want to know what

00:07:49.890 --> 00:07:52.330
T2 is, we need to calculate T.

00:07:52.330 --> 00:07:58.495
And finally we have B. And
what is the forces on B?

00:07:58.495 --> 00:08:03.150
We have T3 minus 2T.

00:08:03.150 --> 00:08:06.260
And again pulley B is 0.

00:08:06.260 --> 00:08:12.400
And so we see that
