00:09:53.760 --> 00:09:55.800
So in principle, we
would have four unknowns

00:09:55.800 --> 00:09:56.980
and three equations.

00:09:56.980 --> 00:10:00.540
Or if we restrict our attention
to these two equations,

00:10:00.540 --> 00:10:05.080
we have three unknowns
and two equations.

00:10:05.080 --> 00:10:11.040
Are unknowns T, A1 and A2.

00:10:11.040 --> 00:10:12.910
These are our unknowns.

00:10:12.910 --> 00:10:16.030
And now our next step
is to try to figure out

00:10:16.030 --> 00:10:19.800
what is the missing
condition that's relating

00:10:19.800 --> 00:10:21.600
the sum of these unknowns.

00:10:21.600 --> 00:10:23.730
And that will be a
constraint condition

00:10:23.730 --> 00:10:26.090
